explicit type annotations ### client annotations `agreementserviceclient` provides annotations for `session.create_client("marketplace-agreement")`. ```python from aiobotocore.session import get_session from types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement import agreementserviceclient session = get_session() async with session.create_client("marketplace-agreement") as client: client: agreementserviceclient # now client usage is checked by mypy and ide should provide code completion ``` ### literals `types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement.literals` module contains literals extracted from shapes that can be used in user code for type checking. full list of `agreementservice` literals can be found in [docs](https://youtype.github.io/types_aiobotocore_docs/types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement/literals/). ```python from types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement.literals import agreementstatustype def check_value(value: agreementstatustype) -> bool: ... ``` ### type definitions `types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement.type_defs` module contains structures and shapes assembled to typed dictionaries and unions for additional type checking. full list of `agreementservice` typedefs can be found in [docs](https://youtype.github.io/types_aiobotocore_docs/types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement/type_defs/). ```python from types_aiobotocore_marketplace_agreement.type_defs import byolpricingtermtypedef def get_value() -> byolpricingtermtypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the PyPI (Python Package Index) page for "types-aiobotocore-marketplace-agreement," a Python library providing type annotations for the aiobotocore.AgreementService 2.12.1 service. The latest version, 2.12.1, was released on March 5, 2024. It is designed to be compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright, facilitating type checking and code completion. The library requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. It is developed by Vlad Emelianov and supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13. The package is part of a broader effort to provide fully type-annotated versions of boto3, botocore, aiobotocore, and aioboto3 libraries, enhancing developer productivity by enabling better static analysis and autocomplete features in IDEs.
